The paper proposes a convolutional neural network-based architecture for watermarking, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with copyright infringement, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses watermarking techniques, which is a sub-topic of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves image processing and geometric distortion, which are sub-topics of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
